74 月 10 㬵 gäo jiāo (same as 交 gäo jiāo) to intersect; the sun and the moon in the sky.⁸ the place where the orbits of the sun and moon cross each other.²⁴ Unicode 3b35; KangXi: page 505, character 21.
Notes: Distinguish these three characters...
(1) 㬵 gäo jiāo with 月 radical; Unicode 3B35; KangXi: page 505, character 21
(2) 胶 vão háo with 肉 radical; Unicode 80F6; KangXi: page 981, character 3. This character is different from #(1) above, even though they may look the same in some fonts.
(3) 胶 gäo jiāo, the simplified form of 膠 gäo jiāo with 肉 radical; Unicode 81A0; KangXi: page 993, character 8. It is the same character as #(2) above, but pronounced differently.
